FILE H1_{MESH_ID} — DATA_PICK_{SIM}_H1_{MESH_ID}.pkl
  Force-chain bars: geometry, normals, and stress resultants along each bar over time.
  (H = horizontal direction bars; MESH_ID e.g. 2000, 2001)
  dict {
    't'                : list[float]  len=75
    'nodes'            : list[dict]  len=8571 (one dict per node)
                           { t_idx (int, 0-based, 0..74) -> node_data }
    'bars'             : dict { bar_id (int, 0-based) ->
                           dict { t_idx (int, 0-based, 0..74) ->
                             dict { 'normals': list[tuple(nx, ny)],
                                    'SS'     : list[tuple(S11, S22, S12)] }
                           }
                         }
    'bars_connectivity': dict { bar_id (int, 0-based) -> list[tuple(node_a, node_b)] }
                           node indices are 0-based
  }

FILE H2_{MESH_ID} — DATA_PICK_{SIM}_H2_{MESH_ID}.pkl
  Tension/compression network graphs (NetworkX) for horizontal bars per time step.
  dict {
    't'          : list[float]  len=75
    'tension'    : dict { t_idx (int, 0-based) -> networkx.Graph }
    'compression': dict { t_idx (int, 0-based) -> networkx.Graph }
  }

FILE H3_BFS_{MESH_ID} — DATA_PICK_{SIM}_H3_BFS_{MESH_ID}.pkl
  Global efficiency (BFS-based) for horizontal force chains per time step.
  dict {
    't'           : list[float]  len=75
    'global_ef_t' : list[float64]  len=75   — efficiency in tension network
    'global_ef_c' : list[float64]  len=75   — efficiency in compression network
  }

================================================================================
FILE I1_{MESH_ID} — DATA_PICK_{SIM}_I1_{MESH_ID}.pkl
  Same structure as H1 but for a denser interpolation mesh (59526 bars, 31874 nodes).
  dict {
    't'                : list[float]  len=75
    'nodes'            : list[dict]  len=31874
                           { t_idx (int, 0-based) -> node_data }
    'bars'             : dict { bar_id (int, 0-based) -> dict { t_idx -> bar_data } }
    'bars_connectivity': dict { bar_id (int, 0-based) -> list[tuple(node_a, node_b)] }
  }

FILE I2_{MESH_ID} — DATA_PICK_{SIM}_I2_{MESH_ID}.pkl
  Same structure as H2 (NetworkX tension/compression graphs) for I-mesh bars.
  dict {
    't'          : list[float]  len=75
    'tension'    : dict { t_idx (int, 0-based) -> networkx.Graph }
    'compression': dict { t_idx (int, 0-based) -> networkx.Graph }
  }

FILE I3_BFS_{MESH_ID} — DATA_PICK_{SIM}_I3_BFS_{MESH_ID}.pkl
  Same structure as H3_BFS for I-mesh bars.
  dict {
    't'           : list[float]  len=75
    'global_ef_t' : list[float64]  len=75
    'global_ef_c' : list[float64]  len=75
  }

================================================================================
FILE J1_{MESH_ID} — DATA_PICK_{SIM}_J1_{MESH_ID}.pkl
  Same structure as H1 but for diagonal/other direction bars (2051 nodes).
  bars_connectivity entries contain multiple node pairs per bar (sub-segments).
  dict {
    't'                : list[float]  len=75
    'nodes'            : list[dict]  len=2051
    'bars'             : dict { bar_id (int, 0-based) -> dict { t_idx -> bar_data } }
    'bars_connectivity': dict { bar_id (int, 0-based) -> list[tuple(node_a, node_b), ...] }
                           NOTE: multiple segments per bar (e.g. (0,276),(276,277),...)
  }

FILE J2_{MESH_ID} — DATA_PICK_{SIM}_J2_{MESH_ID}.pkl
  Same structure as H2 (NetworkX graphs) for J-direction bars.

FILE J3_BFS_{MESH_ID} — DATA_PICK_{SIM}_J3_BFS_{MESH_ID}.pkl
  Same structure as H3_BFS for J-direction bars.

================================================================================
FILE K1_{MESH_ID} — DATA_PICK_{SIM}_K1_{MESH_ID}.pkl
  Extended bar data: includes original Abaqus node IDs and stress per node over time.
  (31874 nodes, 59526 bars — same mesh as I1 but with extra fields)
  dict {
    't'                : list[float]  len=75
    'nodes'            : list[dict]  len=31874
                           { t_idx (int, 0-based) -> node_data }
    'nodes_id'         : list[int]  len=31874   — original Abaqus node IDs (NOT 0 or 1 based;
                                                   raw Abaqus IDs, e.g. first entry = 2)
    'nodes_stress'     : list[dict]  len=75      — one dict per time step
                           { node_idx (int, 0-based) -> stress_value }
    'bars'             : dict { bar_id (int, 0-based) ->
                           dict { t_idx (int, 0-based) ->
                             dict { 'normals': list[tuple], 'SS': list[tuple] }
                           }
                         }
    'bars_connectivity': dict { bar_id (int, 0-based) -> list[tuple(node_a, node_b)] }
                           node indices are 0-based
    'bars_meth2'       : dict { bar_id (int, 0-based) ->
                           dict { t_idx (int, 0-based) -> float }  — alternative stress measure
                         }
  }

FILE K2_{MESH_ID} — DATA_PICK_{SIM}_K2_{MESH_ID}.pkl
  Same structure as H2/I2 (NetworkX tension/compression graphs) for K-mesh bars.

FILE K3_BFS_{MESH_ID} — DATA_PICK_{SIM}_K3_BFS_{MESH_ID}.pkl
  Same structure as H3_BFS/I3_BFS for K-mesh bars.

